1. You know what, Roland?
2. I’ve been feeling ecstatic these days; the memories are fading.
3. Yes. Those cruel times…
4. The things I didn’t want to see are becoming faint; the things I didn’t want to remember are melting away.
5. When I close my eyes, the moments that come to remembrance are of three or four days ago, not one million years in the past.
6. They are the times of my own… claimed through my own choice.
7. And the flow of time is faster than ever for me.
8. I’m no longer shackled to the fetter of perceiving the hours 100 times slower than humans do.
9. I feel happier with each new day, you know?
10. …That, I can’t quite receive with a smile.
11. Still, the despicable man who had locked me up for one million years would fall to despair if he saw what’s happening now.
12. Yes… He’ll endlessly despair.
13. His idiotic and flawed plan caused more people to wallow in agony.
14. He’s going to pay his price in full soon enough.
15. Bring down? No. I told you my aim before.
16. I will become free along with the librarians.
17. On top of that, the Abnormalities that are wandering inside this Library lacking a physical form will be able to leave.
18. Garnering strength by devouring powerful individuals, the Abnormalities would roam the City as they like.
19. That’s what my plan is. I’m setting them free to do whatever they want.
20. And they’ll leave a mark deeper than any Distortion could on the City.
21. The one absolute and perfect book shall be the guide to teach me how to do it all.
22. You’re wrong. There’s a world of difference. I have no interest in the “beauty” that Distortions or Abnormalities can arouse.
23. I simply want them to live as they wish, whether they’re beautiful or unsightly.
24. Besides, even if the Blue Reverberation’s intentions were similar to mine, I would never give away my precious possession to a man like that.
25. That’s what I must do. I was forced to witness countless deaths while reciting a script like a promptress.
26. Such things… are all I could watch and learn. I have to do what I can do well.
27. It’s the only thing I know how to do…
28. I have to feel joy as I witness the fall of the plan devised by the man I love yet hate.
29. Even though it’s not… enjoyable to see the City and its people suffer because of me…
30. I still have to feel happy. I’m obliged to.
31. It’s what I’ve been waiting for… until now…
32. If I don’t do this, I won’t be compensated for the million years of lone suffering—nowhere else would I be repaid…
33. …I still long for vengeance. However…
34. …
35. Forget it. I could spend all day thinking it over, but I’d reach the same conclusion regardless.
36. I’ll find the one book at all costs and make my wish come true.
37. I suppose that’s not a bad idea.
38. And then… As I previously said, I want to travel around the world. It’ll certainly be fun.
39. Once I’ve laid down all the burdens, of course.
